From beff96b7f15ec9b2d384646bac8ccb509fd54bca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ram <chan2006@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 16:48:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] AWS Connect: derive Role ARN from Account ID, no
 copy-paste-back needed
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Symmetric fix to the Azure auto-detect improvement, applied to AWS.
The Role ARN's shape is fully deterministic — it's just
arn:aws:iam::<account_id>:role/ArchAI-ReadOnly-<connection_id>,
and we already control that naming convention. Asking for the
12-digit Account ID upfront (non-secret, easy to find) lets us
compute the exact ARN ourselves, removing the need to copy it back
from CloudFormation's Outputs tab after stack creation.

- app/api/aws-connect/init: now requires account_id (validated as
  exactly 12 digits), computes the Role ARN immediately using the
  same naming convention already proven correct in live testing
  (ArchAI-ReadOnly-<StackName>, matching the CFN template's
  RoleName), and stores it on the connection row right away.
- app/api/aws-connect/confirm: simplified to only need
  connection_id — reads the already-computed role_arn from the DB
  instead of requiring the client to submit it.
- components/brownfield/BrownfieldClient.tsx: added an AWS Account
  ID input before 'Launch Stack' (with a hint on where to find it),
  and removed the Role ARN paste-back field entirely — 'Verify &
  Connect' is now a single click with nothing to copy.
- SQL: added account_id column to aws_connections (migration
  provided separately, additive/non-breaking).

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds, no new lint
errors beyond the one pre-existing no-html-link-for-pages issue.
